Week 2 Report

 What I did this week

1. Data preprocessing

I cleaned and prepared the data for training.

What I did:
- Normalized each sensor channel (mean = 0, std = 1)
- Split data into train (70%), validation (15%), test (15%)
- Made sure same person is not in both train and test

Code file: `src/preprocessing.py`

Results:
| Set | Samples |
|-----|---------|
| Train | 6,384 |
| Validation | 1,368 |
| Test | 1,368 |

2. Baseline model (Random Forest)

I trained a simple Random Forest to compare with deep learning later.

Parameters:
- 100 trees
- Random state = 42

Results on test set:

| Metric | Score |
|--------|-------|
| Accuracy | 84.2% |
| F1-score (macro) | 0.83 |

Confusion matrix findings:
- Easy activities: sitting, standing, lying (95%+ accuracy)
- Hard activities: stairs up vs stairs down (confused 15% of time)
- Running and walking are never confused

 3. Made plots

I saved these plots in `results/` folder:
- Confusion matrix for Random Forest
- Feature importance (top 10 sensors)
- Train/val split distribution

Problems I had

1.Normalization - Different people have different signal ranges. I normalized per channel, not per person.

2. Data leakage - At first I split randomly. Some people appeared in train AND test. That is bad because model would recognize the person, not the activity. I fixed it by splitting by subject ID.

